Privacy Policy
We take the privacy and security of our users very seriously. This privacy policy sets out how we collect, use, and protect any information you provide using our gaming services.
Information We Collect
When you use our gaming services, we may collect the following types of information:
Personal Information
: We may collect personal information, such as your name, email address, and date of birth, when you create an account with us.
Game Information
: We may collect information about your gaming activity, including your progress, achievements, and gameplay statistics.
Device Information
: We may collect information about the devices you use to access our gaming services, including the type of device when we collect feedback.
Usage Information
: We may collect information about how you use our gaming services, such as the pages you visit, the features you use, and the time and date of your activity.
How We Use Information
We use the information we collect to provide and improve our gaming services. Specifically, we may use your information for the following purposes:
To operate and maintain our gaming services.
To personalize your experience and provide you with relevant content.
To communicate with you about our gaming services, including updates, promotions, and events.
To conduct research and analysis to improve our gaming services.
To protect our users and our gaming services from fraud, abuse, and other illegal activities.
How We Protect Your Information
We take reasonable steps to protect your information from unauthorized access, disclosure, or destruction. Specifically, we use industry-standard security measures, such as encryption, to protect your information.
We also limit access to your information to those employees, agents, and contractors who need to know the information to operate, develop, or improve our gaming services.
Profile Deletion
We aim to keep our information about you accurate. You can terminate your account any time you want. We want to reassure you that when you delete your account, all of your personal data will be permanently deleted from our servers. This includes any information you have provided to us, such as your name, email address, and any other personal details. We believe that protecting your data is of the utmost importance, and we take great care to ensure that it is completely removed from our system.
Detailed instructions on how to delete your personal data can be accessed via
this page
. Please note that this action is irreversible and your account along with all your personal data will be deleted permanently. For any inquiries, please contact us at
support@bhoos.com
.
Disclosure of Your Information
We may disclose your information to third parties in the following circumstances:
With your consent
To comply with legal obligations, such as a court order or subpoena
To prevent fraud, abuse, or other illegal activities
To protect the rights, property, or safety of our users or others
Third-Party Services
Our gaming services may include links to third-party websites or services. These third-party services have their own privacy policies, and we are not responsible for their content or privacy practices.
Child Protection
Bhoos.com does not knowingly collect or use personal information from any player under the age of 13. If you are under the age of 13 years, please do not register at Bhoos.com or send any of your information to us. We will permanently delete any information from players below 13 years of age.
Cookies
We may send you a temporary cookie when you visit our site or use our gaming services. A cookie is a small file of a text-only string of information that can be embedded in your computer so that we can remember who you are when you revisit our site. We may use the data generated from cookies to compile data on your use at our website. You are not obliged to accept our cookies and can decline cookies by modifying the settings in your browser.
Changes To Our Privacy Policy
We may amend this statement at any time and immediately effect by updating this page of the Privacy Policy. We will seek to notify you of any changes beforehand. If we cannot do so, you must review any changes in this Privacy Policy page periodically.
Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about our privacy policy, please get in touch with us at
support@bhoos.com
.